pokemon.name: Bulbasaur
pokemon.pokedex_entry: For some time after its birth, it uses the nutrients that are packed into the seed on its back in order to grow.

pokemon.name: Ivysaur
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The more sunlight Ivysaur bathes in, the more strength wells up within it, allowing the bud on its back to grow larger.

pokemon.name: Venosaur
pokemon.pokedex_entry: While it basks in the sun, it can convert the light into energy. As a result, it is more powerful in the summertime.

pokemon.name: Charmander
pokemon.pokedex_entry: If Charmander is healthy, the flame on the tip of its tail will burn vigorously and won’t go out even if it gets a bit wet.

pokemon.name: Charmeleon
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It is very hotheaded by nature, so it constantly seeks opponents to battle against. Its aggression will not be quelled if it doesn’t win.

pokemon.name: Charizard
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It uses its wings to fly sky-high. The more experience it gains in battle, the greater the temperature at which its flames burn.

pokemon.name: Squirtle
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its shell is soft immediately after it is born. In no time at all, the shell becomes so resilient that a prodding finger will bounce right off it.

pokemon.name: Wartortle
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Wartortle’s long, furry tail is a symbol of longevity, so this Pokémon is quite popular among older people.

pokemon.name: Blastoise
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It has jet nozzles on its shell. This impressive Pokémon uses these jets to charge toward foes with all the force of a rocket.

pokemon.name: Caterpie
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

pokemon.name: Metapod
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Even though it is encased in a sturdy shell, the body inside is tender. It can’t withstand a harsh attack.

pokemon.name: Butterfree
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It loves the nectar of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.

pokemon.name: Weedle
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.

pokemon.name: Kakuna
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.

pokemon.name: Beedrill
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

pokemon.name: Pidgey
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.

pokemon.name: Pidgeotto
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.

pokemon.name: Pidgeot
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This Pokémon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.

pokemon.name: Rattata
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.

pokemon.name: Raticate
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

pokemon.name: Spearow
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.

pokemon.name: Fearow
pokemon.pokedex_entry: A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.

pokemon.name: Ekans
pokemon.pokedex_entry: A very common sight in grasslands and such. It flicks its tongue in and out to sense danger in its surroundings.

pokemon.name: Arbok
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.

pokemon.name: Pikachu
pokemon.pokedex_entry: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

pokemon.name: Raichu
pokemon.pokedex_entry: When its electricity builds, its muscles are stimulated, and it becomes more aggressive than usual.

pokemon.name: Sandshrew
pokemon.pokedex_entry: No matter how high a place it falls from, this Pokémon can save itself by rolling into a ball and bouncing.

pokemon.name: Sandslash
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The spikes on its body are made up of its hardened hide. It rolls up and attacks foes with its spikes.

pokemon.name: Nidoran (F)
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It uses its hard incisor teeth to crush and eat berries. The tip of a female Nidoran’s horn is a bit more rounded than the tip of a male’s horn.

pokemon.name: Nidorina
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The horn on its head has atrophied. It’s thought that this happens so Nidorina’s children won’t get poked while their mother is feeding them.

pokemon.name: Nidoqueen
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It pacifies offspring by placing them in the gaps between the spines on its back. The spines will never secrete poison while young are present.

pokemon.name: Nidoran (M)
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The horn on a male Nidoran’s forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokémon, always straining its large ears.

pokemon.name: Nidorino
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It’s nervous and quick to act aggressively. The potency of its poison increases along with the level of adrenaline present in its body.

pokemon.name: Nidoking
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Nidoking prides itself on its strength. It’s forceful and spirited in battle, making use of its thick tail and diamond-crushing horn.

pokemon.name: Clefairy
pokemon.pokedex_entry: On nights with a full moon, they gather together and dance. The surrounding area is enveloped in an abnormal magnetic field.

pokemon.name: Clefable
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It has an acute sense of hearing. It can easily hear a pin being dropped nearly 1,100 yards away.

pokemon.name: Vulpix
pokemon.pokedex_entry: As its body grows larger, its six warm tails become more beautiful, with a more luxurious coat of fur.

pokemon.name: Ninetales
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It has nine long tails and fur that gleams gold. It is said to live for 1,000 years.

pokemon.name: Jigglypuff
pokemon.pokedex_entry: If it inflates to sing a lullaby, it can perform longer and cause sure drowsiness in its audience.

pokemon.name: Wigglytuff
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The rich, fluffy fur that covers its body feels so good that anyone who feels it can’t stop touching it.

pokemon.name: Zubat
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies around with skill.

pokemon.name: Golbat
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It loves to drink other creatures’ blood. It’s said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood it’s gathered.

pokemon.name: Oddish
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its scientific name is Oddium wanderus. It is said to cover distances as far as 1,000 feet when night falls, walking on its two roots.

pokemon.name: Gloom
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn’t drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

pokemon.name: Vileplume
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The bud bursts into bloom with a bang. It then starts scattering allergenic, poisonous pollen.

pokemon.name: Paras
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

pokemon.name: Parasect
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The bug host is drained of energy by the mushroom on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.

pokemon.name: Venonat
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Poison oozes from all over its body. It catches small bug Pokémon at night that are attracted by light.

pokemon.name: Venomoth
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.

pokemon.name: Diglett
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its skin is very thin. If it is exposed to light, its blood heats up, causing it to grow weak.

pokemon.name: Dugtrio
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow.

pokemon.name: Meowth
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It loves things that sparkle. When it sees a shiny object, the gold coin on its head shines, too.

pokemon.name: Persian
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It has a vicious temperament. Beware if it raises its tail straight up. This is a signal that it is about to pounce and bite.

pokemon.name: Psyduck
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.

pokemon.name: Golduck
pokemon.pokedex_entry: When it swims at full speed using its long, webbed limbs, its forehead somehow begins to glow.

pokemon.name: Mankey
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.

pokemon.name: Primape
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.

pokemon.name: Growlithe
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

pokemon.name: Arcanine
pokemon.pokedex_entry: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.

pokemon.name: Poliwag
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its legs are newly grown, and it can’t walk very well. It seems to prefer swimming through the water instead.

pokemon.name: Poliwhirl
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its skin is moist all over its body. The skin on its belly spiral also feels smooth.

pokemon.name: Poliwrath
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Although it’s skilled in a style of dynamic swimming that uses all its muscles, for some reason it lives on dry land.

pokemon.name: Abra
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Abra can teleport in its sleep. Apparently the more deeply Abra sleeps, the farther its teleportations go.

pokemon.name: Kadabra
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This Pokémon’s telekinesis is immensely powerful. To prepare for evolution, Kadabra stores up psychic energy in the star on its forehead.

pokemon.name: Alakazam
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

pokemon.name: Machop
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

pokemon.name: Machoke
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.

pokemon.name: Machamp
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It punches with its four arms at blinding speed. It can launch 1,000 punches in two seconds.

pokemon.name: Bellsprout
pokemon.pokedex_entry: No matter what Bellsprout is doing, if it detects movement nearby, it will immediately react by reaching out with its thin vines.

pokemon.name: Weepinbell
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Even though it is filled with acid, it does not melt because it also oozes a protective fluid.

pokemon.name: Victreebel
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Once taken into Victreebel's body, even the hardest object will be melted into nothing by the Pokémon's acid.

pokemon.name: Tentacool
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its eyes are as transparent as crystals. From them, it shoots mysterious beams of light.

pokemon.name: Tentacruel
pokemon.pokedex_entry: On the rare occasions that large outbreaks of Tentacruel occur, all fish Pokémon disappear from the surrounding sea.

pokemon.name: Geodude
pokemon.pokedex_entry: At rest, it looks just like a rock. Carelessly stepping on it will make it swing its fists angrily.

pokemon.name: Graveler
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Moss-covered rocks are Graveler’s favorite food. It consumes over a ton of them a day, crunching loudly while it eats.

pokemon.name: Golem
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It is enclosed in a hard shell that is as rugged as slabs of rock. It sheds skin once a year to grow larger.

pokemon.name: Ponyta
pokemon.pokedex_entry: About an hour after birth, Ponyta’s fiery mane and tail grow out, giving the Pokémon an impressive appearance.

pokemon.name: Rapidash
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It gallops at nearly 150 mph. With its mane blazing ferociously, it races as if it were an arrow.

pokemon.name: Slowpoke
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.

pokemon.name: Slowbro
pokemon.pokedex_entry: If the tail-biting Shellder is thrown off in a harsh battle, this Pokémon reverts to being an ordinary Slowpoke.

pokemon.name: Magnemite
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges electromagnetic waves and so on from the units at its sides.

pokemon.name: Magneton
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.

pokemon.name: Farfetch'd
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It can’t live without the stalk it holds. That’s why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.

pokemon.name: Doduo
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its heads never sleep at the same time—each one takes a turn keeping watch while the other sleeps, switching every hour or so.

pokemon.name: Dodrio
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It now has three hearts and three sets of lungs. Though it can’t run as fast as Doduo, Dodrio can keep running for longer stretches of time.

pokemon.name: Seel
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The colder it gets, the better it feels. It joyfully swims around oceans so cold that they are filled with floating ice.

pokemon.name: Dewgong
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It stores thermal energy in its body to fend off the cold. It swims at eight knots even in frigid waters.

pokemon.name: Grimer
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Born from sludge, these Pokémon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.

pokemon.name: Muk
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It’s thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

pokemon.name: Shellder
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.

pokemon.name: Cloyster
pokemon.pokedex_entry: When attacked, it launches its spikes in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.

pokemon.name: Gastly
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its body is made of gas. Despite lacking substance, it can envelop an opponent of any size and cause suffocation.

pokemon.name: Haunter
pokemon.pokedex_entry: In total darkness, where nothing is visible, Haunter lurks, silently stalking its next victim.

pokemon.name: Gengar
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Hiding in people’s shadows at night, it absorbs their heat. The chill it causes makes the victims shake.

pokemon.name: Onix
pokemon.pokedex_entry: As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.

pokemon.name: Drowzee
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children’s are much tastier.

pokemon.name: Hypno
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Always holding a pendulum that it swings at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in anyone nearby.

pokemon.name: Krabby
pokemon.pokedex_entry: If it senses danger approaching, it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.

pokemon.name: Kingler
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The larger pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.

pokemon.name: Voltorb
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

pokemon.name: Electrode
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

pokemon.name: Exeggcute
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Using telepathy only fellow Exeggcute can pick up on, they always form a cluster of six.

pokemon.name: Exeggutor
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It is said that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an Exeggcute.

pokemon.name: Cubone
pokemon.pokedex_entry: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.

pokemon.name: Marowak
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.

pokemon.name: Hitmonlee
pokemon.pokedex_entry: At the exact moment it lands a kick on its target, Hitmonlee hardens the muscles on the sole of its foot, maximizing the power of the kick.

pokemon.name: Hitmonchan
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It corners its foes with combo punches from both sides, then finishes them off with a single straight punch launched at over 300 mph.

pokemon.name: Lickitung
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Bug Pokémon are Lickitung’s main food source. This Pokémon paralyzes its prey with a lick from its long tongue, then swallows the prey whole.

pokemon.name: Koffing
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The poisonous gases it contains are a little bit lighter than air. That’s why it’s always slightly airborne.

pokemon.name: Weezing
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Top-grade perfume is made using its internal poison gases by diluting them to the highest level.

pokemon.name: Rhyhorn
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Once it starts running, it won’t stop—even if it crashes through boulders. This disposition is what’s caused its habitat to expand.

pokemon.name: Rhydon
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The horn of a Rhydon is powerful enough to crush raw diamonds. These Pokémon polish their horns by bashing them together.

pokemon.name: Chansey
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This kindly Pokémon lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

pokemon.name: Tangela
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon’s true appearance remains a mystery.

pokemon.name: Kangaskhan
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Although it’s carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.

pokemon.name: Horsea
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It maintains balance using its tail, which is wound up like a coil. It may spray ink from its mouth.

pokemon.name: Seadra
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The male raises the young. If it is approached while caring for young, it will use its toxic spines to fend off the intruder.

pokemon.name: Goldeen
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its dorsal and pectoral fins are strongly developed like muscles. It can swim at a speed of five knots.

pokemon.name: Seaking
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Using its horn, it bores holes in riverbed boulders, making nests to prevent its eggs from washing away.

pokemon.name: Staryu
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Fish Pokémon nibble at it, but Staryu isn’t bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.

pokemon.name: Starmie
pokemon.pokedex_entry: At the center of its body is a red core that sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.

pokemon.name: Mr. Mime
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Emanations from its fingertips solidify the air into invisible walls that repel even harsh attacks.

pokemon.name: Scyther
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.

pokemon.name: Jynx
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It seductively wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.

pokemon.name: Electabuzz
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its body constantly discharges electricity. Getting close to it will make your hair stand on end.

pokemon.name: Magmar
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather’s body temperature is nearly 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Pinsir
pokemon.pokedex_entry: These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.

pokemon.name: Tauros
pokemon.pokedex_entry: They fight each other by locking horns. The herd’s protectors take pride in their battle-scarred horns.

pokemon.name: Magikarp
pokemon.pokedex_entry: An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.

pokemon.name: Gyarados
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

pokemon.name: Lapras
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Able to understand human speech and very intelligent, it loves to swim in the sea with people on its back.

pokemon.name: Ditto
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It can freely recombine its own cellular structure to transform into other life-forms.

pokemon.name: Eevee
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element stones.

pokemon.name: Vaporeon
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its cell composition is similar to water molecules. As a result, it can’t be seen when it melts away into water.

pokemon.name: Jolteon
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.

pokemon.name: Flareon
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Porygon
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Porygon is an artificial Pokémon created using advanced scientific means. It can move freely through cyberspace.

pokemon.name: Omanyte
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is a member of an ancient, extinct species. Omanyte paddles through water with its 10 tentacles, looking like it’s just drifting along.

pokemon.name: Omastar
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Weighed down by a large and heavy shell, Omastar couldn’t move very fast. Some say it went extinct because it was unable to catch food.

pokemon.name: Kabuto
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This species is almost entirely extinct. Kabuto molt every three days, making their shells harder and harder.

pokemon.name: Kabutops
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Kabutops slices its prey apart and sucks out the fluids. The discarded body parts become food for other Pokémon.

pokemon.name: Aerodactyl
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This is a ferocious Pokémon from ancient times. Apparently even modern technology is incapable of producing a perfectly restored specimen.

pokemon.name: Snorlax
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This gluttonous Pokémon eats constantly, apart from when it’s asleep. It devours nearly 900 pounds of food per day.

pokemon.name: Articuno
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This legendary bird Pokémon can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

pokemon.name: Zapdos
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This legendary Pokémon is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

pokemon.name: Moltres
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It is one of the legendary bird Pokémon. Its appearance is said to indicate the coming of spring.

pokemon.name: Dratini
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It sheds many layers of skin as it grows larger. During this process, it is protected by a rapid waterfall.

pokemon.name: Dragonair
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It is called the divine Pokémon. When its entire body brightens slightly, the weather changes.

pokemon.name: Dragonite
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It can fly in spite of its big and bulky physique. It circles the globe in just 16 hours.

pokemon.name: Mewtwo
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its DNA is almost the same as Mew’s. However, its size and disposition are vastly different.

pokemon.name: Mew
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Mew is said to possess the genetic composition of all Pokémon. It is capable of making itself invisible at will, so it entirely avoids notice even if it approaches people.

pokemon.name: Chikorita
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its pleasantly aromatic leaf has the ability to check the humidity and temperature of the area around it.

pokemon.name: Bayleef
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The scent that wafts from the leaves on its neck causes anyone who smells it to become energetic.

pokemon.name: Meganium
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Meganium’s breath holds within it the power to revive grasses and plants that have withered.

pokemon.name: Cyndaquil
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The fire that spouts from its back burns hottest when it is angry. The flaring flames intimidate foes.

pokemon.name: Quilava
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The fur covering this Pokémon’s body never burns, no matter what. It can shrug off any kind of fire attack.

pokemon.name: Thyplosion
pokemon.pokedex_entry: If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.

pokemon.name: Totodile
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This rough critter chomps at any moving object it sees. Turning your back on it is not recommended.

pokemon.name: Croconaw
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It opens its huge jaws wide to attack. If it loses fangs while biting, they’ll just keep on growing back, one after another.

pokemon.name: Ferligatr
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Although it has a massive body, its powerful hind legs enable it to move quickly, even on land.

pokemon.name: Sentret
pokemon.pokedex_entry: If it encounters a foe, it will stand up on its tail, making itself look bigger than usual to intimidate them.

pokemon.name: Furret
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It raises its offspring inside a long, narrow nest. Once they’re old enough, it takes them outside the nest to prepare them for independence.

pokemon.name: Hoothoot
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Since it tells time precisely, some countries consider it to be a deity of wisdom, versed in the ways of the world.

pokemon.name: Noctowl
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.

pokemon.name: Ledyba
pokemon.pokedex_entry: These very cowardly Pokémon join together and use Reflect to protect their nest.

pokemon.name: Ledian
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It flies through the night sky, sprinkling sparkly dust. According to some, if that dust sticks to you, good things will happen to you.

pokemon.name: Spinarak
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Even while there are prey ensnared in its nest of spun thread, Spinarak will wait motionlessly until darkness falls.

pokemon.name: Aridos
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It wanders in search of food after darkness falls, never nesting in a specific place.

pokemon.name: Crobat
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This Pokémon flaps its four wings skillfully. Crobat can fly through cramped caves without needing to slow down.

pokemon.name: Chinchou
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It lives in ocean depths beyond the reach of sunlight. It flashes lights on its antennae to communicate with others of its kind.

pokemon.name: Lanturn
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It blinds prey with an intense burst of light. With the prey incapacitated, the Pokémon swallows it in a single gulp.

pokemon.name: Pichu
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Despite this Pokémon’s cute appearance, those who want to live with one should prepare to be on the receiving end of its electric jolts.

pokemon.name: Cleffa
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Since it is often seen when shooting stars fill the night skies, it’s said to come here by riding on a star.

pokemon.name: Igglybuff
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its body has a faintly sweet scent and is bouncy and soft. If it bounces even once, it cannot stop.

pokemon.name: Togepi
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It is considered to be a symbol of good luck. Its shell is said to be filled with happiness.

pokemon.name: Togetic
pokemon.pokedex_entry: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.

pokemon.name: Natu
pokemon.pokedex_entry: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.

pokemon.name: Xatu
pokemon.pokedex_entry: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

pokemon.name: Mareep
pokemon.pokedex_entry: If static electricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.

pokemon.name: Flaafy
pokemon.pokedex_entry: As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won’t grow.

pokemon.name: Ampharos
pokemon.pokedex_entry: When it gets dark, the light from its bright, shiny tail can be seen from far away on the ocean’s surface.

pokemon.name: Bellossom
pokemon.pokedex_entry: After it grows up, it leaves the forest it was born in to form groups with other Bellossom. It breaks into dance when it gets excited.

pokemon.name: Marill
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry even when it plays in the water.

pokemon.name: Azumarill
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.

pokemon.name: Sudowoodo
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation.

pokemon.name: Politoed
pokemon.pokedex_entry: If Poliwag and Poliwhirl hear its echoing cry, they respond by gathering from far and wide.

pokemon.name: Hoppip
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Outside of cold regions, Hoppip can be found practically everywhere. This is because the wind carries this species all over the world.

pokemon.name: Skiploom
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Skiploom enthusiasts can apparently tell where a Skiploom was born by the scent drifting from the flower on the Pokémon’s head.

pokemon.name: Jumpluff
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Jumpluff travels on seasonal winds. Once its cotton spores run out, its journey ends, as does its life.

pokemon.name: Aipom
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its tail moves with greater dexterity than its hands. Making deft use of this tail, Aipom lives high among the treetops.

pokemon.name: Sunkern
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. Knowing it’s weak, it simply feeds until it evolves.

pokemon.name: Sunflora
pokemon.pokedex_entry: In the daytime, it rushes about in a hectic manner, but it comes to a complete stop when the sun sets.

pokemon.name: Yanma
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It can see in all directions without moving its big eyes, helping it spot both attackers and prey right away.

pokemon.name: Wooper
pokemon.pokedex_entry: A transparent mucous membrane covers its body. Touching it bare-handed will cause a tingling numbness.

pokemon.name: Quagsire
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Due to its relaxed and carefree attitude, it often bumps its head on riverbed boulders and boat hulls as it swims.

pokemon.name: Espeon
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its enemy’s actions.

pokemon.name: Umbreon
pokemon.pokedex_entry: When darkness falls, the rings on the body begin to glow, striking fear in the hearts of anyone nearby.

pokemon.name: Murkrow
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

pokemon.name: Slowking
pokemon.pokedex_entry: When its head was bitten, toxins entered Slowpoke’s head and unlocked an extraordinary power.

pokemon.name: Misdreavus
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This Pokémon startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

pokemon.name: Unown A
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.

pokemon.name: Wobbuffet
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to pump up its counterstrike.

pokemon.name: Girafarig
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Though very small, the brain in its tail is still considered an important organ because it emits powerful psychic energy.

pokemon.name: Pineco
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It spits out a fluid that it uses to glue tree bark to its body. The fluid hardens when it touches air.

pokemon.name: Forretress
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It’s usually found hanging on to a fat tree trunk. It shoots out bits of its shell when it sees action.

pokemon.name: Dunsparce
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted, it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.

pokemon.name: Gligar
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It builds its nest on a steep cliff. When it is done gliding, it hops along the ground back to its nest.

pokemon.name: Steelix
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.

pokemon.name: Snubbul
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its growls make its opponents uneasy. This laid-back Pokémon tends to sleep half the day.

pokemon.name: Granbull
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It is actually timid and easily spooked. If attacked, it desperately flails its limbs about in an attempt to repel its opponent.

pokemon.name: Qwilfish
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Be cautious if this Pokémon starts sucking in water—it will soon attack by scattering the toxic spikes that grow all over its body.

pokemon.name: Scisor
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It swings its eye-patterned pincers up to scare its foes. This makes it look like it has three heads.

pokemon.name: Shuckle
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

pokemon.name: Heracross
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It loves sweet nectar. To keep all the nectar to itself, it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.

pokemon.name: Sneasel
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This is a smart and sneaky Pokémon. A pair may work together to steal eggs by having one lure the parents away.

pokemon.name: Teddiursa
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its paws are soaked in oodles of honey. When nervous, Teddiursa will lick its paws and soon have a smile back on its face.

pokemon.name: Ursaring
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It usually wears a hardened expression, but when it’s licking up honey—which it loves—the joy it feels will cause it to break into a wide grin.

pokemon.name: Slugma
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its lava body can cool and chip away at times, but a magma bath will heal it right up.

pokemon.name: Macargo
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This Pokémon lives near the craters of volcanoes. It stores fire energy in its shell of cooled and hardened magma.

pokemon.name: Swinub
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It searches for food by digging into the ground with its snout. Even frozen ground doesn’t give it any trouble.

pokemon.name: Piloswine
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.

pokemon.name: Corsola
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can’t live in polluted waters.

pokemon.name: Remoraid
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The water they shoot from their mouths can hit moving prey from more than 300 feet away.

pokemon.name: Octillery
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

pokemon.name: Delibird
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It carries food all day long. There are tales about lost people who were saved by the food it had.

pokemon.name: Mantine
pokemon.pokedex_entry: If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can jump out above the waves and glide for over 300 feet.

pokemon.name: Skarmory
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Because it nests in bramble bushes, the feathers of its chicks grow hard from being scratched by thorns.

pokemon.name: Houndour
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

pokemon.name: Houndoom
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.

pokemon.name: Kingdra
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is said to sleep at the bottom of the sea—deeper than any other life-form can descend—building its energy.

pokemon.name: Phanpy
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This Pokémon lives and nests on a riverbank. After playing in the mud, it won’t be able to settle down unless it washes its body.

pokemon.name: Donphan
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Donphan is normally a calm Pokémon, but once it is enraged, it will curl its body into a ball and charge at you while rolling.

pokemon.name: Porygon2
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Porygon was upgraded to become capable of planetary development. However, this upgraded version cannot even fly yet.

pokemon.name: Stantler
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It’s said that this Pokémon used to be stronger long ago when it had many enemies, and that it was even able to evolve under its own power.

pokemon.name: Smeargle
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Once a Smeargle reaches adulthood, it will have other members of its species leave paw prints on its back.

pokemon.name: Tyrogue
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Its intense desire to become stronger and stronger drives it to recklessly train its body and challenge any opponent it can find to battle.

pokemon.name: Hitmontop
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is adept at dance-like kicks. The horn atop its head is made from the same substance that generally forms fur and claws.

pokemon.name: Smoochum
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This is a very curious Pokémon. Smoochum decides what it likes and dislikes by touching things with its lips.

pokemon.name: Elekid
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It loves violent thunder. The space between its horns flickers bluish white when it is charging energy.

pokemon.name: Magby
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Magma-like blood circulates throughout this Pokémon’s body, raising its body temperature as high as 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Miltank
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Miltank produces highly nutritious milk, so it’s been supporting the lives of people and other Pokémon since ancient times.

pokemon.name: Blissey
pokemon.pokedex_entry: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.

pokemon.name: Raikou
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

pokemon.name: Entei
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.

pokemon.name: Suicune
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

pokemon.name: Larvitar
pokemon.pokedex_entry: It is born deep underground. It can’t emerge until it has entirely consumed the soil around it.

pokemon.name: Pupitar
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This pupa flies around wildly by venting with great force the gas pressurized inside its body.

pokemon.name: Tyranitar
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It is so insolent that it doesn’t care about others.

pokemon.name: Lugia
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Lugia’s wings pack devastating power—a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this Pokémon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.

pokemon.name: Ho-oh
pokemon.pokedex_entry: Ho-Oh’s feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

pokemon.name: Celebi
pokemon.pokedex_entry: This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.
